The paper focuses on keyword search on Knowledge Graphs (KGs), which is a common topic in Information Retrieval (IR) and Database (DB) research. The proposed approach also involves scoring and weighting schemes, which are commonly used in Artificial Intelligence (AI) and Machine Learning (ML) research. The paper also mentions the use of parallel execution, which is a topic in Distributed Computing (DC) and Large Scale Data Processing (LG). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.IR and cs.DB, followed by cs.AI, cs.DL, and cs.LG.
